OL,6,FCouncillor Carol Mould, portfolio
OL,7,Fholder for Neighbourhoods at Cornwall
OL,8,FCouncil, said: "We want everyone to
OL,9,Fenjoy our beautiful beaches but please
OL,10,Fbe responsible. If you want to have a
OL,11,FBBQ, check the rules for wherever you
OL,12,Fare and don't put it in the bin unless
OL,13,Fit is completely extinguished."
OL,15,FCouncillor Martyn Alvey, the portfolio
OL,16,Fholder responsible for Cornwall Fire
OL,17,Fand Rescue Service, added: "Incidents
OL,18,Finvolving BBQs and outdoor fires can
OL,19,Fquickly spread and become out of
OL,20,Fcontrol.
